&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 X 25 HOUR POST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 X 24 HOUR POST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited to join our dynamic telephone booking team in the Referral &amp; Booking Centre at St Woolos Hospital, Newport. You will be trained to deal with the many calls coming into the department from patients. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be supported in the role by a Team Leader and full in-house training will be given by our own trainer internal to the department. The role is fast paced and interesting, we actively encourage in-house education through the NVQ route. Candidates with proven customer service experience , particularly in a Call Centre environment, are required to support the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in Health records is desirable for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Saturday morning working on a rota system will be expected once fully trained.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gareth Gough - Referral &amp; Booking Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;gareth.gough@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01495 765407&lt;/p&gt;
